{"award_age":56.0,"bio_image":"full\/09bf57b7117a6f4d5dc2ae74bca92ce7f7db481d.jpg","category":"Peace","country":"United States","date_of_birth":"1914-03-25T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":"2009-09-12T00:00:00.000Z","gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/b\/ba\/Norman_Borlaug.jpg\/220px-Norman_Borlaug.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Norman_Borlaug","mini_bio":"<p><b>Norman Ernest Borlaug<\/b> (March 25, 1914\u00a0\u2013 September 12, 2009)<sup id=\"cite_ref-APDeath_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Norman_Borlaug#cite_note-APDeath-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> was an American <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Biologist\" title=\"Biologist\">biologist<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Humanitarian\" title=\"Humanitarian\" class=\"mw-redirect\">humanitarian<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Peace_Prize\" title=\"Nobel Peace Prize\">Nobel laureate<\/a> who has been called \"the father of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Green_Revolution\" title=\"Green Revolution\">Green Revolution<\/a>\",<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Norman_Borlaug#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> \"<a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Agriculture\" title=\"Agriculture\">agriculture<\/a>'s greatest spokesperson\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Norman_Borlaug#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> and \"The Man Who Saved A Billion Lives\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Norman_Borlaug#cite_note-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Norman_Borlaug#cite_note-6\"><span>[<\/span>6<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He is one of seven people to have won the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Peace_Prize\" title=\"Nobel Peace Prize\">Nobel Peace Prize<\/a>, the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Presidential_Medal_of_Freedom\" title=\"Presidential Medal of Freedom\">Presidential Medal of Freedom<\/a> and the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Congressional_Gold_Medal\" title=\"Congressional Gold Medal\">Congressional Gold Medal<\/a><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Norman_Borlaug#cite_note-7\"><span>[<\/span>7<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> and was also awarded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Padma_Vibhushan\" title=\"Padma Vibhushan\">Padma Vibhushan<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/India\" title=\"India\">India<\/a>'s second highest civilian honor.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Norman_Borlaug#cite_note-8\"><span>[<\/span>8<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>Borlaug received his B.Sc. Biology 1937 and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Doctor_of_Philosophy\" title=\"Doctor of Philosophy\">Ph.D.<\/a> in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Plant_pathology\" title=\"Plant pathology\">plant pathology<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Genetics\" title=\"Genetics\">genetics<\/a> from the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Minnesota\" title=\"University of Minnesota\">University of Minnesota<\/a> in 1942. He took up an agricultural research position in Mexico, where he developed semi-dwarf, high-<a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Crop_yield\" title=\"Crop yield\">yield<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Phytopathology\" title=\"Phytopathology\" class=\"mw-redirect\">disease<\/a>-resistant <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wheat\" title=\"Wheat\">wheat<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Variety_(biology)\" title=\"Variety (biology)\" class=\"mw-redirect\">varieties<\/a>.<\/p><p>During the mid-20th century, Borlaug led the introduction of these high-yielding varieties combined with modern agricultural production techniques to Mexico, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Pakistan\" title=\"Pakistan\">Pakistan<\/a>, and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/India\" title=\"India\">India<\/a>. As a result, Mexico became a net exporter of wheat by 1963. Between 1965 and 1970, wheat yields nearly doubled in Pakistan and India, greatly improving the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Food_security\" title=\"Food security\">food security<\/a> in those nations.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Norman_Borlaug#cite_note-9\"><span>[<\/span>9<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> These collective increases in yield have been labeled the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Green_Revolution\" title=\"Green Revolution\">Green Revolution<\/a>, and Borlaug is often credited with saving over a billion people worldwide from <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Starvation\" title=\"Starvation\">starvation<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-fn_1_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Norman_Borlaug#cite_note-fn_1-10\"><span>[<\/span>10<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He was awarded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Peace_Prize\" title=\"Nobel Peace Prize\">Nobel Peace Prize<\/a> in 1970 in recognition of his contributions to <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/World_peace\" title=\"World peace\">world peace<\/a> through increasing food supply.<\/p><p>Later in his life, he helped apply these methods of increasing food production to Asia and Africa.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Juan_Enriquez_TED_Talk_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Norman_Borlaug#cite_note-Juan_Enriquez_TED_Talk-11\"><span>[<\/span>11<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Norman Borlaug","place_of_birth":"Saude , near  Cresco ,  Iowa ,  United States","place_of_death":"Dallas ,  Texas ,  United States","text":"Norman Borlaug , Peace, 1970","year":1970.0}